This paper is primarily focused on object detection and localization using computer vision techniques, which falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the use of machine learning algorithms for learning multi-scale templates, which is relevant to the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of visual features and the importance of discriminative information, which are relevant to the sub-categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper discusses the experimental analysis and performance evaluation, which is relevant to the sub-category of information retrieval (cs.IR).
